  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink6-kilavi"> kaḷaviṉiṟ palanāḷoḻuki vantu varaintukoṇṭa talaimakaṉ tōḻiyōṭu collāṭi,
          ‘yāṉ varaiyātu oḻukukiṉṟa nāḷ nīyir iṅku iḻaittirunta tiṟam yātu?’ eṉṟāṟku avaḷ colliyatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Aink6">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> vēntupakai taṇika yāṇṭupala nantuka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> malarnta poykai mukainta tāmarait</l>
          <l> taṇṭuṟai yūraṉ varaika</l>
          <l> ventaiyuṅ koṭukka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">

<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May the king's enemies calm down! May he flourish for many years!' </l>
<l>          That's what mother our wants. As for us: </l>
<l>          'The man from the village by the cool ghat,</l>
<l>          where lotuses have formed buds in the blooming pond: </l>
<l>          May he propose marriage! </l>
<l>          And may our father give [his consent]!' — that's what we want.</l>
          
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
